<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>3224</id>
    <title>Some WAP browsers failing to redirect to callback url.</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Some Sony Mobile Phones fail to redirect to the API callback url_ and/or the  Next  Parameter in the following api call.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">http://m.facebook.com/login.php?api_key=mykey&amp;next=http://www.myurl.com/facebook&amp;v=1.0</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Once a Sony Java Based phone logs in to the above link_ authorizing my third party app_ it is never redirected to the callback url listed.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">Instead it just leaves the user on their facebook mobile page.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Symbian based phones do not have the problem_ and are redirected properly as long as a GET request is used with  hidden  paramaters for the api calls_ as listed in the forums here.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">http://forum.developers.facebook.com/viewtopic.php?id=15707</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">I have tried to use POST and get for this request.</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">With and without the Next parameter (attempting to use the Callback url defined in the Facebook App settings)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">I believe it to be some type of malformed HTML that the Sony WAP browser does not understand_ but troubleshooting is tough since we cannot see what facebook is attempting to send the phone for redirect.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">All we see is a refresh of the users mobile facebook page.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">Cameron</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
